  <title type="text">tar a file without ancestor directories</title>
  <link rel="alternate" href="http://kejia.github.io/blog/2002/03/26/tar-a-file-without-ancestor-directories/?utm_source=all&amp;utm_medium=Atom" />
  <id>urn:http-kejia-github-io:-blog-2002-03-26-tar-a-file-without-ancestor-directories</id>
  <published>2002-03-26T21:51:15Z</published>
  <updated>2002-03-26T21:51:15Z</updated>
  <author>
   <name>柯嘉 | kejia</name></author>
  <content type="html">&lt;html&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;tar&lt;/code&gt; command may generate a file with unnecessary ancestor directories. use &lt;code&gt;C&lt;/code&gt; option to remain the file only:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="brush: bash"&gt;
 &lt;table class="sourcetable"&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
   &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td class="linenos"&gt;
     &lt;div class="linenodiv"&gt;
      &lt;pre&gt;1&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td class="code"&gt;
     &lt;div class="source"&gt;
      &lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;tar -czf xi.tar.gz -C /one/two/three/xi .
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</content></entry></feed>